# ARG Scheduler Layer — Module Kconfig

config SCHAD_ARG_KMM
	tristate "ARG Scheduler Module (SCHAD_ARG_KMM)"
	depends on SCHAD_ARG
	depends on SMP
	depends on ARM64
	default m
	help
	  ARG (Architecture Runtime Group) Scheduler Layer.

	  Contains 95% of the ARG project logic:
	    - Task packing (reduces active CPU count, saves energy)
	    - Async mode  (gaming / FPS stability)
	    - Sync mode   (throughput / batch workloads)
	    - Virtual Thread layer (large task decomposition)
	    - ARM64 feature-aware dispatch
	    - big.LITTLE topology support
	    - CPU hotplug support

	  Depends on SCHAD_ARG (the kernel hook in kernel/sched/).
	  Can be loaded and unloaded at runtime without rebooting.

	  Say M to build as a loadable module (recommended).
	  Say Y to build into the kernel.
	  Say N to disable completely.
